</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Let=E2=80=99s see:</p><ul style=3D"lis=
t-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">In 2016, Revlon Inc. borrowed $1.8 billion from some ban=
ks and hedge funds using a seven-year <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9=
lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDA4ODc5MjEvMDAwMTU2NzYxOTE2MDAyOTE5L3MwMDE0MDl4MV84ay5odG=
0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8e254d05" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> term loan</a> secured by Revl=
on=E2=80=99s assets. Citibank NA advised on the loan and served as its admi=
nistrative agent.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In 2019 and 2020=
, Revlon took some of the collateral for the 2016 term loan and snuck it ou=
t, away from the lenders: It put much of its intellectual property, includi=
ng brands like American Crew, Elizabeth Arden, Almay and Mitchum, into new =
subsidiaries (generally called =E2=80=9CBrandCo=E2=80=9D) that did not secu=
re the 2016 loan. It <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAw=
MDA4ODc5MjEvMDAwMDk1MDE0MjIwMDAxMTA5L2VoMjAwMDYyOV84ay5odG0/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB77813dda" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> borrowed some new money</a>=C2=A0secured by =
those brands, and rolled some of the old term lenders into the new facility=
 in order to get them to vote to approve it. There were various shenanigans=
 involved, including doing a new revolving loan under the 2016 credit agree=
ment in order to get just enough votes to approve the new deal. We have dis=
cussed <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28128683.26=
1603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMD=
cvZGlzdHJlc3NlZC1kZWJ0LWRlYWwtbWFrZXMtcGVvcGxlLW1hZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjIxMjJfT=
U9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVy=
bT0yMjA2MjEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2f1679=
58" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  the basic form of this</a> many <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTEvdGVycmEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYyM=
TIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRt=
X3Rlcm09MjIwNjIxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7=
44c8c46" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  times</a> before: If you are a company in trouble, you p=
ay off 51% of your lenders to get them to approve hosing the other 49%. Tha=
t=E2=80=99s what happened here: Revlon gave some of its lenders a new loan =
with better security (those brands), making the security for the other lend=
ers worse. (This is explained in more detail <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cua3NsYXcuY29tL2F0=
dGFjaG1lbnRzLzAwMC8wMDgvMTc4L29yaWdpbmFsL1JldmxvbiVFMiU4MCU5OXNfQnJhbmRDb1N=
waW4tT2ZmX19vcl9KLl9DcmV3X1JldmlzaXRlZC5wZGY_MTU5OTIzNDY4OA/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB483e01f1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> here</a>.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">The 2016 lenders who didn=E2=80=99t participate in the new BrandCo =
deal were annoyed: Their collateral had disappeared, and now they were effe=
ctively junior to the 2020 lenders. They <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1=
bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3J2Y0xWcGRBcjRRVS92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB0cdac811" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> sued</a> Revlon, Citibank and various other people,=
 claiming that the BrandCo deal violated the 2016 credit agreement and was =
invalid. If they won =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I dunno, it would be a mess if they won=
, but generally speaking if they won then they would get those brands back =
as collateral for their loans.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The=
 day before they filed that lawsuit, Citi paid them off by accident. Oops! =
This was very funny and we have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMTcvY2l0aS1jYW4tdC1oYXZlLWl0cy05MDAtbWlsbGlvbi1iYWNr=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MjEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB2611efae" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked about it a lot</a>, but the gi=
st is that Citi, as administrative agent for the loan, was supposed to pass=
 along a small interest payment from Revlon and accidentally paid off the w=
hole loan with its own money.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Citi=
 politely asked the 2016 lenders for the money back, but the lenders were r=
eally mad at Citi for helping with the BrandCo transaction, so some of them=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0who had gotten about $500 million of Citi=E2=80=99s money =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0said no.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Citi sued =
them and, somewhat shockingly, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMTcvY2l0aS1jYW4tdC1oYXZlLWl0cy05MDAtbWlsbGlvbi1iYWNrP=
2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MjEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1u=
ZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cC2611efae" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  lost</a>.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">Citi appealed. I assume Citi will win on appeal, but the=
n I assumed they=E2=80=99d win in the trial court so who knows. The appeal =
is still pending and could take a while.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">Meanwhile the thing everyone worried about happened, and Revlon file=
d for bankruptcy last week.</li></ul><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This rais=
es various wild questions. For instance: Who are the creditors on the 2016 =
term loan, now? There are three main options:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-ty=
pe: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;"><em>Citi: </em>Citi paid off that $500 million on Revlon=E2=80=
=99s behalf,=C2=A0so it presumably steps into the shoes of those creditors =
and has a $500 million bankruptcy claim against Revlon. (This is probably n=
ot worth $500 million: My Bloomberg screen shows the 2016 term loan trading=
 below 30 cents on the dollar, while the 2020 BrandCo term loan looks to be=
 in the 50s.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"><em>The original len=
ders:</em> Maybe Citi will win on appeal, in which case the lenders=C2=A0wi=
ll have to give back Citi=E2=80=99s $500 million, in which case Revlon will=
 still owe them the money. =E2=80=9CLawyers for the repaid lenders in the b=
ankruptcy court hearing on Thursday described their clients as only =E2=80=
=98contingent creditors=E2=80=99 who since they have already been repaid wi=
ll not need to participate in the bankruptcy fight unless the appeals court=
 orders them to return the cash to Citi,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28128683.261603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2N=
vbnRlbnQvOTcxNzVmM2UtMjlhZS00ZGNlLTllYTgtNDFjYmRhY2NkOTQ3P3NoYXJlVHlwZT1ub2=
5naWZ0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd0c16b85" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reports Sujeet Indap</a=
> at the Financial Times. But since it will presumably take a while to find=
 out, they continue to have some interest in the case.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;"><em>Nobody:=C2=A0Did</em> Citi pay that $500 million o=
n Revlon=E2=80=99s behalf? Or did it pay the $500 million out of the goodne=
ss of its heart, discharging Revlon=E2=80=99s obligation to the term lender=
s but not creating any new obligation to Citi? That seems ridiculous, but o=
n the other hand Revlon=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>in bankruptcy so it has an in=
centive =E2=80=94=C2=A0an obligation, almost =E2=80=94=C2=A0to minimize its=
 debt load.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Jerem=
y Hill and Eliza Ronalds-Hannon <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
